Cross-reaction of the 84 mAbs with human tissue was screened via microarray immunohistochemical staining. Our results showed that four mAb clones were cross-reactive with human tissue, of which 2 (A1-10 and H1-84) reacted with human brain tissue and 2 (H1-55 and H1-17) with pancreatic tissue (see Table 4
). The A1-10 monoclonal antibody reacted with tissues of the cerebral cortex and the nucleus of horny, whereas H1-17 and H1-55 reacted with islet α cells (Fig. 1
).
